		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Lancaster</placeName> <date>May 28th 1857</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p>Respected Sir<lb/>  We have<lb/> the frankness of directing a few<lb/> lines to you hoping they will receive<lb/> your notice.  Being informed that<lb/> your Congregation have contemplated<lb/> to erect a new house of worship<lb/> <sic>wich</sic> is to be <sic>handsomly</sic> finished&#44;<lb/> we have made it an object of<lb/> inquiry to <sic>asertain</sic> from you&#44;<lb/> <sic>wherter</sic> your intention is to have<lb/> any decorative painting executed<lb/> at the interior walls &#38; ceilings of it&#44;<lb/> and <sic>wherter</sic> that part of the work<lb/> has been <sic>allready</sic> awarded to some<lb/> person or not&#63;  If not&#44; will you<lb/> please and inform us&#33;&#95;&#95;.  We are<lb/> anxious to give you a proposal&#44;<lb/> and would politely request you to<lb/> pardon our boldness &#40;as <sic>perhapps</sic><lb/> entire strangers to you&#41; in introduce&#95;<lb/>ing <sic>ourselfs</sic> as Decorative Painters<lb/> in Fresco&#44; Encaustic and oil colours&#44;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>Twenty years practical experience<lb/> &#40;with many <sic>recomendations</sic> of the<lb/> most trustworthy men from all<lb/> parts of this and adjoining states&#41;<lb/> warrants us in saying that&#44; we are<lb/> able to execute painting entrusted<lb/> to us&#44; in a <sic>maner</sic> not to be<lb/> <sic>exceded</sic>&#44; and <sic>supscribe</sic> <sic>ourselfs</sic> as<lb/> Respectfully Yours</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Geo. &#38; John J. Seiling</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
		</body>
